{
  "id": "17cd7ea387d30ac3",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/skelar/84405c43-e205-4cfd-ae14-a1ffa3c19158/application",
    "company": "skelar",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "17cd7ea387d30ac3",
    "department": "Support",
    "description": "[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/3a2721ac-0cf6-4bb5-a785-483b8d1018c3/Ashby_header.png]\n\nAt Liven, we’re building one of the most human-centered self-discovery platforms in the U.S. With over 2.3 million users, our mission is to guide people through emotional challenges using thoughtful features and trusted voices.\n\nAs part of our team, you'll help shape in-app content that reaches hundreds of thousands—whether it’s short videos, expert advice, or co-creating features that really make a difference. Your face, voice, and knowledge will become a safe space for users navigating tough emotions.\n\nWe’re seeking licensed mental health professionals (LCSW, LPCC, LMFT, Psychologist, PsyD, or equivalent) who are passionate about mental well-being and excited to bring their expertise to a wider audience.\n\nIf you love sharing helpful insights, enjoy being on camera, and want to make mental health support more accessible through digital tools—this opportunity is for you!\n\nWhat You’ll Do:\n— Create short-form video content offering guidance, tips, and emotional support;\n— Contribute ideas and insights to help shape app content and features;\n— Collaborate with the Liven team on new content formats (e.g., webinars, in-app guides, digital workshops);\n— Share therapeutic knowledge in an accessible, compassionate way;\n— Ensure content aligns with ethical standards and evidence-based practices.\n\n\nRequirements:\n— Licensed or pre-licensed to practice independently (LCSW, LPCC, LMFT, PsyD, etc.);\n— 4+ years of clinical experience;\n— Comfortable speaking on camera (mobile phone recording is fine);\n— Stable internet connection and ability to meet remotely;\n— Strong written and spoken English;\n— A desire to make mental health support more personal, relatable, and scalable.\n\n\nThis position is for you if...\n—You are a therapist looking to diversify your work beyond 1:1 sessions;\n— You are a clinician who is passionate about education, prevention, and outreach;\n— You are a creator who want to bring healing tools into everyday lives through accessible content;\n— You believe that mental health support should be both professional and human.\n\nLet's create something valuable together!\n\n[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/bf8afb62-59f5-436b-b500-74f06bd0bb6e/Ashby_footer_eng.png]",
